snippet.textDisplay:
Under cooked. Under-whelming. Manages to make you appreciate Nescafe Basement's take on Pee Jaon all the more... that's saying a lot when Pee Jaon is anyway one of the most favorite NB songs... 
QB and Shuja both under-utilized as vocalists. Music too disjointed and fragmented. It's a given that no-one does smooth transition better than Rohail Hayat, but that doesn't mean others can't do half as good a job. 
And yes, I went there - for the first time this season, I mentioned Rohail Hayat.
snippet.textOriginal:
